```

Actual behavior:
crashes because currently [Actions.find](https://main-api.flutter.dev/flutter/widgets/Actions/find.html) returns `Action<T>`.  We are able to find `Action<U>` where `T :< U` (and verify that in debug mode), but casting the `Action<U>` to `Action<T>` would result in a runtime crash.



Options:
1. ignore this and wait for [contravariance to be added](https://github.com/dart-lang/language/issues/214)
2. change the return type to `Action<Intent>`
3. deprecate `maybeFind` and `find` and redirect people to [invoke](https://main-api.flutter.dev/flutter/widgets/Actions/invoke.html).

